Introduction:
	Java concurrency is a term that covers multithreading, concurrency and parallelism on the java platform. That includes the Java concurrency tools, problems and solutions.
This java concurrency tutorial covers the core concepts of multithreading, concurrency constructs, concurrency problems, costs, benefits related to multithreading in Java.

What is Multithreading?
	Multithreading means that you have multiple threads of execution inside the same application. A thread is like a separate CPU executing you application. Thus, a multithreaded 
application is like an application that has multiple CPUs executing different parts of the code at the same time.
